INSERT INTO `articles` VALUES (14,'Privacy Policy','<p>This Privacy Policy was last modified on June 19, 2014.</p>\n\n<p>Kids On The Move (&ldquo;us&rdquo;, &ldquo;we&rdquo;, or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates www.kotm.org (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;). This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information we receive from users of the Site.</p>\n\n<p>We use your Personal Information only for providing and improving the Site. By using the Site, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy. Unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy, terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, accessible at www.kotm.org.</p>\n\n<h4>Information Collection And Use</h4>\n\n<p>While using our Site, we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you. Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to, your name, email address, postal address and phone number (&ldquo;Personal Information&rdquo;).</p>\n\n<h4>Log Data</h4>\n\n<p>Like many site operators, we collect information that your browser sends whenever you visit our Site (&ldquo;Log Data&rdquo;). This Log Data may include information such as your computer&rsquo;s Internet Protocol (&ldquo;IP&rdquo;) address, browser type, browser version, the pages of our Site that you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on those pages and other statistics.</p>\n\n<h4>Cookies</h4>\n\n<p>Cookies are files with small amount of data, which may include an anonymous unique identifier. Cookies are sent to your browser from a web site and stored on your computer&rsquo;s hard drive.</p>\n\n<p>Like many sites, we use &ldquo;cookies&rdquo; to collect information. You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you do not accept cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Site.</p>\n\n<h4>Security</h4>\n\n<p>The security of your Personal Information is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>\n\n<h4>Links To Other Sites</h4>\n\n<p>Our Site may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. If you click on a third party link, you will be directed to that third party&rsquo;s site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit.</p>\n\n<p>Kids On The Move has no control over, and assumes no responsibility for, the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third party sites or services.</p>\n\n<h4>Changes To This Privacy Policy</h4>\n\n<p>Kids On The Move may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on the Site. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.</p>\n\n<h4>Contact Us</h4>\n\n<p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please&nbsp;<a href=\"/contact\">contact us</a>.</p>\n','privacy-policy','2021-01-30 10:15:01','2021-01-30 10:34:12','Kids On The Move Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy was last modified on June 19, 2014. Kids On The Move (“us”, “we”, or “our”) operates www.kotm.org (the “Site”). This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information we receive from users of the','logo.png',1,0,'green','page',0),(15,'Legal','<p>Although care has been taken to provide complete and accurate information, the material in this website is provided without guarantee of accuracy or usability. You should consult with your physician or other licensed professional when making decisions about the health care and development of your child.</p>\n','legal','2021-01-30 10:35:37','2021-01-30 10:35:37','Although care has been taken to provide complete and accurate information, the material in this website is provided without guarantee of accuracy or usability. You should consult with your physician or other licensed professional when making decisions about the health care and development of your child.','logo.png',1,0,'green','page',NULL),(18,'thank you!','<p>If you have any questions about your donation please contact us at devoffice@kotm.org.</p>\n','donation-complete','2021-02-10 13:41:36','2021-05-04 15:14:39','','5230_92.jpg',3024,0,'green','page',28),(19,'NOORDA RESOURCE LIBRARY','<h3>KIDS ON THE MOVE HAS A SPECIALTY LIBRARY OF CHILD DEVELOPMENT RESOURCES WITH AN IN-DEPTH COLLECTION ON:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Child development</li>\n	<li>Childhood disabilities</li>\n	<li>Children&rsquo;s books to help children learn about and understand disabilities</li>\n	<li>Special education laws, family rights</li>\n	<li>Including children with disabilities in regular education settings.</li>\n	<li>Advocating for children with disabilities</li>\n	<li>Parenting</li>\n	<li>Intervention strategies</li>\n	<li>Special education</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Everyone is welcome to use KOTM materials on-site. Families currently enrolled for KOTM services have free checkout privileges, but must register. General public&nbsp;wanting checkout must pay a $12 annual membership fee with their registration.&nbsp;Register in person with the librarian during regular operating hours.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4>LIBRARY HOURS</h4>\n\n<p>Tuesday, Thursday, Friday:&nbsp;10 am &ndash;&nbsp;3 pm<br />\nWednesday: 10 am &ndash; 5pm</p>\n','noorda-resource-library','2021-02-11 12:08:03','2021-02-24 11:58:54','','IMG_9906.jpg',1,0,'green','page',29),(20,'monthly donor club','<h3>What is the Monthly Donor Club?</h3>\n\n<p>The Friends of KOTM Monthly Donor Club is a club consisting of our generous recurring donors. These are individuals who have signed up to contribute at least $25 each month to KOTM. These committed members of the Monthly Donor Club receive exciting benefits!&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Those who join KOTM&rsquo;s Monthly Donor Club will be part of a group that receives:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>\n	<p>An official Monthly Donor Club certificate in the mail</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Their name on a special display in the KOTM Orem building</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Exclusive KOTM swag</p>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>Special recognition</p>\n	</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h3>How to Join the Monthly Donor Club</h3>\n\n<p><strong>To join the Monthly Donor Club, email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:kids@kotm.org\">kids@kotm.org</a>&nbsp;and mention that you&#39;d like to make a recurring donation of $25+ to Kids On The Move.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>After 12 months of continuous donations, your name will be added to Kids On The Move&rsquo;s Monthly Donor Club list! You will be notified of your membership via a letter and certificate sent to the mailing address you provided.</p>\n\n<p><em>*Note: Monthly donations must be above $25.00 in order to receive the benefits of the Friends of KOTM Monthly Donor Club</em></p>\n\n<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"mailto:kids@kotm.org?subject=Monthly%20Donor%20Club&amp;body=I\'d%20like%20to%20sign%20up%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20Monthly%20Donor%20Club!%20Please%20let%20me%20know%20what%20is%20needed%20from%20me%20to%20sign%20up%20to%20donate.%20\">Join Monthly Donor Club</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','monthly-donor-club','2021-02-12 09:25:33','2021-03-26 10:58:26','The best way to help Kids On The Move is through monthly recurring donations. Join our monthly donor club today!','2021-02-10-11-03-pexels-bruna-saito-1805843.jpg',3024,0,'green','page',30),(21,'Donate Supplies','<p>Kids On The Move welcomes in-kind donations of materials and services which we would typically need to purchase, including professional services, office supplies, office equipment, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Thank you for showing an interest in helping Kids On the Move. To donate materials, we would ask that you call <a href=\"tel:801-221-9930\">801-221-9930</a> ext 100&nbsp;in advance of bringing in donations.</p>\n\n<p>Here is a list of things we always need at our center:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Child Art Supplies: &nbsp;Paper, washable markers/paint, glue sticks, fat crayons, chalk, crafty items</li>\n	<li>Diapers and wipes</li>\n	<li>New outdoor playground toys/equipment</li>\n	<li>New children&rsquo;s books, toys, games, puzzles, etc.</li>\n	<li>General hygiene items for families:&nbsp; toothpaste, toothbrushes, soap, shampoo/conditioner, hand sanitizer, lotion, Kleenex, cotton balls, q-tips, toilet paper, etc.</li>\n	<li>General cleaning supplies for families:&nbsp; dish soap, laundry soap, household cleaners, paper towels, etc.</li>\n	<li>General supplies for use at KOTM: air freshener, paper towels, lotion in pump dispenser for restrooms, hand sanitizer, Clorox wipes, Kleenex, etc.</li>\n	<li>General office supplies in constant use at KOTM:&nbsp; standard white copy paper, blue/black pens, post-it notes</li>\n	<li>Gift certificates or gift cards</li>\n	<li>Towel bibs (we have a pattern)</li>\n	<li>Cases of bottled water</li>\n	<li><strong>RESPITE CARE supplies: </strong>Goldfish crackers, Welch&rsquo;s fruit snacks (Welch&#39;s has the preferred texture for our clients and is gluten free), water bottles, popular board games, and new hard plastic toys with no small pieces.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We also have a book with a variety of projects that you are welcome to come by and look through.</p>\n\n<h3>Eagle Scout Projects</h3>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/2021-02-20-20-22-Eagle-Scout-Project.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>Each year over 50 scouts do their Eagle Scout Project for Kids On The Move. Some projects in the past have included:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Making toys and other developmental tools</li>\n	<li>Collecting materials</li>\n	<li>Making Christmas gifts</li>\n	<li>Sponsoring events</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>If you are interested in doing your Eagle Scout Project with us, please come into our Orem location &ndash; <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/YsYS4kfYpb5g8gRZ9\">475 West 260 North Orem, Utah 84057</a></strong></p>\n\n<p>Ask our receptionist for the Eagle Scout Binder that has a list of current available projects as they are always changing.</p>\n\n<p>We are open Monday-Friday, 8 am &ndash; 5 pm and would love to discuss your possible options.</p>\n','donate-supplies','2021-02-22 09:14:13','2021-04-15 14:40:48','','logo.png',3024,0,'green','page',NULL),(22,'COVID-19 Notice','<p>Due to the COVID-19 virus outbreak, most Kids On The Move&rsquo;s programs are gradually reopening for the safety of our employees and the families we serve.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The KOTM staff will continue reaching out to all families receiving services in each of our programs by whatever means possible in an effort to continue supporting children and&nbsp;families throughout the public closure.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you for your patience and understanding during this time.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<p>Please call our regular number&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:801.221.9930\"><strong>801.221.9930</strong></a>&nbsp;if you have any questions concerning any of the KOTM programs.</p>\n\n<p>NOTE: This number cannot receive text message requests. You may use the &lsquo;KOTM Live Chat Now&rsquo; chat button for live support online.</p>\n\n<p>These support channels will be actively monitored between 8:00 am &ndash; 5:00 pm.</p>\n','covid-19-notice','2021-02-22 09:34:28','2021-02-24 12:00:08','Due to the COVID-19 virus outbreak, most Kids On The Move’s programs are gradually reopening for the safety of our employees and the families we serve.','2021-02-22-09-16-kelly-sikkema-r2hTBxEkgWQ-unsplash.jpg',1,1,'green','article',NULL),(23,'Community Partners','<h4>Thank you to our community partners who have donated their time, services, and resources to help us empower families, one child at a time.&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/2021-02-23-12-35-community partners logos, final.jpg\" style=\"height:244px; width:700px\" /></p>\n','community-partners','2021-02-22 09:42:42','2021-02-25 13:57:52','','logo.png',3024,0,'green','page',NULL),(25,'MONTHLY DONOR CLUB DISPLAY','<p>This past month, our lobby received an exciting new addition. A special display was constructed to honor the members of our Monthly Donor Club - a group of individuals who have set up recurring monthly donations to KOTM. We are so grateful for all the contributions we receive, and especially appreciate the recurring donations that best help our organization to thrive. Check out the details of how we presented this special display to our Monthly Donor Club members:</p>\n\n<p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DuNxXFlUg4s?rel=0\" width=\"640\"></iframe></p>\n\n<p><strong>To join the Monthly Donor Club, email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:kids@kotm.org\">kids@kotm.org</a>&nbsp;and mention that you&#39;d like to make a recurring donation&nbsp;to Kids On The Move.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>After 12 months of continuous donations, your name will be added to Kids On The Move&rsquo;s Monthly Donor Club list! You will be notified of your membership via a letter and certificate sent to the mailing address you provided and your name will be added to our mirror display.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://kotm.org/article/monthly-donor-club\">Learn More about the Monthly Donor Club</a></p>\n','monthly-donor-club-display','2021-03-26 10:43:30','2021-03-26 10:58:05','This past month, our lobby received an exciting new addition. A special display was constructed to honor the members of our Monthly Donor Club - a group of individuals who have set up recurring monthly donations to KOTM. Check out this special display that we constructed to honor the impact that reoccurring contributions provide!','2021-03-26-10-23-Monthly donor club mirror display edit.jpeg',3024,1,'green','article',NULL),(26,'NEW RUN - KOTM Run For Autism 2022','<p>Kids On The Move recently announced that as of March 31, 2021, the KOTM Autism Center has withdrawn from the Heber Half race.</p>\n\n<p>We know that autism is very near and dear to your hearts as it is to our hearts as well. The separation from the Heber Half race does not lessen our responsibility to the autism community. Future events are in the works to reinforce an even greater commitment to each of you.&nbsp;KOTM plans to grow and expand our influence with the autism community in a significant way that will continue to educate, support, and inspire for years to come.</p>\n\n<p>We are pleased to announce our&nbsp;Kids On The Move Run for Autism; coming 2022!</p>\n\n<p>100% of the KOTM Run For Autism race proceeds will go toward serving children in our KOTM Autism Center.</p>\n\n<p>Our greatest strength comes from our community. We are building our race committee and we would love to have you join us. If you are interested in joining us, or would like to sign up as a future volunteer or committee member for the race, please email our development department at:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:development@kotm.org\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">development@kotm.org</a>.&nbsp;Additionally,&nbsp;we would like to ask for your financial donation/sponsorship.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>We are grateful for your continued support, and we are excited for you to&nbsp;Experience the Full Heart of Kids On The Move&nbsp;and participate in this upcoming fantastic race.</p>\n','new-run---kotm-run-for-autism-2022','2021-03-31 11:17:23','2021-03-31 11:17:31','Kids On The Move recently announced that as of March 31, 2021, the KOTM Autism Center has withdrawn from the Heber Half race.','2021-03-31-11-16-pexels-jonas-mohamadi-1416736.jpg',3024,1,'green','article',NULL);
