INSERT INTO `pages` VALUES (1,'/about','About Us','Kids On The Move continues to provide high quality, comprehensive services to young children and families in our community.','About, history, programs','2021-05-05 13:02:06',3024,'about-us.jpg','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(2,'/about/board','Board of Directors','Kids On The Move Board Of Directors volunteer their time and expertise to the organization.','board, board of directors','2021-04-14 10:34:27',3024,'IMG_9968.jpg','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,'/donate','Donate','Your generous donation helps support thousands of children and families throughout Utah. Monetary amounts make it possible for Kids On The Move to continue making a difference in the lives of individuals in need. The donations you contribute to KOTM make it so that families are a little better today than they were yesterday.','give, donate, donation, donations, gift','2021-05-03 10:40:40',3024,'IMG_3769.jpg','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(4,'/events','Events','This is the events page',NULL,'2021-01-21 15:43:39',1,'logo.png','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'/give','Give','Kids On The Move is part of a great community that has supported us since 1986. Each year, we rely on donations of time, money, and materials to supplement the state and federal grants that support our families and children. We welcome and need your involvement!','give, donation, donate','2021-02-25 15:40:14',1,'IMG_4321.png','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(6,'/home','Home','Kids On The Move in Utah is a nonprofit organization dedicated to empowering families, one child at a time. Our programs are: Autism Center, Child Care, Early Head Start, Early Intervention, and Respite Care. We provide important services for children with disabilities throughout Utah via telehealth and in-center learning opportunities.','home, main','2021-04-26 12:03:27',3024,'logo.png','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(7,'/programs/autism-center','Autism Center','The Kids On The Move Autism Center provides individualized services throughout the state of Utah. We serve children ages 2 and up living with Autism Spectrum Disorders (ASD) or similar developmental delays. We have both in-center and telehealth services available.','autism, clinic, program, aba, therapy, center, services, bcba, telehealth, peers','2022-07-18 07:49:03',1,'autism-center.jpg','red','program',NULL,NULL),(8,'/programs/child-care','Child Care','Our affordable Orem, UT Child Care Center in Utah County is a fully-licensed program committed to providing high quality daycare for children from 6 weeks to first grade enrollment. Our Kids On The Move Child Care Center is located in Utah County.','child care, childcare, daycare, day care, enroll, orem, child care pricing, child care orem, orem child care, affordable child care','2021-04-30 08:35:19',3024,'child-care.jpg','purple','program',NULL,NULL),(9,'/programs/early-head-start','Early Head Start','The Kids On The Move Early Head Start program in Utah serves pregnant mothers and children birth to three years of age by providing resources in the community and educational topics on health, nutrition, safety, parenting, and development.','early head start, ehs, development, infants, baby, babies, spanish','2021-03-19 12:15:01',3024,'2021-02-09-11-49-pexels-filipe-leme-2760338.jpg','green','program',NULL,NULL),(10,'/programs/early-intervention','Early Intervention','Kids On The Move Early Intervention is based throughout the state of Utah and provides services to children under the age of three with a significant developmental delay.','early intervention, delay, development, baby, down syndrome, diagnosis, assessment','2021-03-19 12:15:37',3024,'pexels-photo-286625.jpg','orange','program',NULL,NULL),(11,'/programs/learning-opportunities','Learning Opportunities','Kids On The Move offers an array of learning opportunities and impactful classes for children, teens, and families.','classes, class, calendar, learning, peers, great beginnings, music and movement, step-families','2021-04-22 14:34:32',1,'2021-02-09-11-49-pexels-agung-pandit-wiguna-1128316.jpg','teal','program',NULL,NULL),(12,'/programs/respite-care','Respite Care','The Kids On The Move Respite Care program provides the families of children with special needs a 3 hour break on weekend nights so caregivers can relieve stress, renew energy, and restore balance. Respite Care in-person services are provided at multiple locations throughout Utah.','respite, respite care, special needs, break, disability, babysit','2021-04-15 15:06:18',3024,'respite.jpg','blue','program',NULL,NULL),(14,'/volunteer-portal','Volunteer Portal','This is the Volunteer Portal',NULL,'2021-01-21 15:43:39',1,'logo.png','green',NULL,NULL,NULL),(30,'/article/privacy-policy','Privacy Policy','Kids On The Move Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy was last modified on June 19, 2014. Kids On The Move (“us”, “we”, or “our”) operates www.kotm.org (the “Site”). This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use and disclosure of Personal Information we receive from users of the','privacy, privacy policy, legal','2021-01-30 10:34:12',1,'logo.png','green','article',NULL,NULL),(31,'/article/legal','Legal','Although care has been taken to provide complete and accurate information, the material in this website is provided without guarantee of accuracy or usability. You should consult with your physician or other licensed professional when making decisions about the health care and development of your child.','legal','2021-01-30 10:35:37',1,'logo.png','green','article',NULL,NULL),(38,'/article/donation-complete','Donation Complete','','','2021-05-04 15:14:39',3024,'5230_92.jpg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(39,'/article/noorda-resource-library','NOORDA RESOURCE LIBRARY','KIDS ON THE MOVE HAS A SPECIALTY LIBRARY OF CHILD DEVELOPMENT RESOURCES WITH AN IN-DEPTH COLLECTION ON:\nChild development\nChildhood disabilities\nChildren’s books to help children learn about and understand disabilities\nSpecial education laws, family rights\nIncluding children with disabilities in regular education settings.\nAdvocating for children with disabilities\nParenting\nIntervention strategies\nSpecial education\nEveryone is welcome to use KOTM materials on-site. Families currently enrolled for KOTM services have free checkout privileges, but must register. General public wanting checkout must pay a $12 annual membership fee with their registration. Register in person with the librarian during regular operating hours.','library, noorda, resource, books, development','2021-02-24 11:58:54',1,'IMG_9906.jpg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(40,'/article/monthly-donor-club','monthly donor club','The best way to help Kids On The Move is through monthly recurring donations. Join our monthly donor club today!','monthly donor club, donations, donate, recurring, friends of KOTM','2021-03-26 10:58:26',3024,'2021-02-10-11-03-pexels-bruna-saito-1805843.jpg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(43,'/article/donate-supplies','Donate Supplies','Kids On The Move welcomes in-kind donations of materials and services which we would typically need to purchase, including professional services, office supplies, office equipment, etc. \n\nThank you for showing an interest in helping Kids On the Move. To donate materials, we would ask that you call 801-221-9930 ext 100 in advance of bringing in donations.','donation, give, donate, supplies, toys, eagle scout, projects, service','2021-04-15 14:40:48',3024,'logo.png','green','article',NULL,NULL),(44,'/article/covid-19-notice','COVID-19 Notice','Due to the COVID-19 virus outbreak, most Kids On The Move’s programs are gradually reopening for the safety of our employees and the families we serve.','covid, 19, coronavirus, virus, pandemic','2021-02-24 12:00:08',1,'2021-02-22-09-16-kelly-sikkema-r2hTBxEkgWQ-unsplash.jpg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(45,'/article/community-partners','Community Partners','THANK YOU TO OUR COMMUNITY PARTNERS WHO HAVE DONATED THEIR TIME, SERVICES, AND RESOURCES TO HELP US EMPOWER FAMILIES, ONE CHILD AT A TIME.','community partners, company donation','2021-02-25 13:57:52',3024,'logo.png','green','article',NULL,NULL),(55,'/form/early-intervention','Apply for Early Intervention','To apply for Early Intervention services through Kids On The Move:\r\n\r\nYOU MUST reside in the Alpine School District boundaries (Orem, Vineyard, Lindon, Pleasant Grove, American Fork, Highland, Cedar Hills, Alpine, Lehi, Saratoga Springs, Eagle Mountain, some parts of Draper)\r\nIt must be 45 days before your child turns 3 years of age. If your child is over this age, please call the Alpine School District Assessment Center at 801.610.8216 for a free assessment.\r\nYou should be contacted by Kids On The Move in FIVE working days. If you have not been contacted in that time, please call us at 801.221.9930.','early intervention, application, apply','2021-02-24 19:48:06',1,'logo.png','orange','form',NULL,NULL),(56,'/form/early-head-start','Prenatal Early Head Start Application','Please fill out this form to apply for the Early Head Start program. You will need be able to turn in a proof of income and a Birth Certificate or Medicaid/Insurance Card to complete the process of application.\r\n\r\nELIGIBILITY\r\nChild under 3 years old\r\nPregnant Women\r\nFamily resides in Utah County\r\nFamily is low income or the child has a disability\r\nWAITING LIST\r\nEarly Head Start is funded to serve only 164 families at a time. When there is no space available, families are placed on a waiting list in order of need. Risk factors are weighted so that families with more need can move more quickly to the head of the line. We will call families on the wait list when there is an opening in the program.\r\n\r\nWHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU APPLY?\r\nWe will call you to set up an Eligibility meeting in which we will collect any needed documentation and review risk factors and needs. After this appointment you will be placed on the waitlist.\r\nWhen there is an opening we will call you and inform you of the potential start date.\r\nWe will call you to set up your first appointment.\r\nTO SUBMIT THE APPLICATION:\r\nClick the “submit” button to send your application on-line. You may also print and mail it to us at 475 West 260 North, Orem, 84057.','early head start, ehs, application, apply','2021-02-26 19:48:06',1,'logo.png','green','form',NULL,NULL),(58,'/contact','Contact Us','mail us now so that we may respond to your questions or concerns!','contact, contact us, phone, email, call, address','2021-02-26 19:48:06',1,'logo.png','green','form',NULL,NULL),(59,'/form/step-families','Step Families Class','Join us for a FREE educational program focusing on issues unique to stepfamily relationships. Concurrent classes for adults and youth 6-18. Free child care for children 5 and under and FREE dinner is included.  Contact Aprille Cecil at acecil@kotm.org for more information.','step, stepfamilies, step families, stepfamily, step family, family, families, class','2021-02-26 19:48:06',1,'logo.png','green','form',NULL,NULL),(60,'/article/monthly-donor-club-display','MONTHLY DONOR CLUB DISPLAY','','monthly donor club, donations, donate, mirror, lobby, building, display, may life reflect the generosity you give','2021-03-26 10:58:05',3024,'2021-03-26-10-23-Monthly donor club mirror display edit.jpeg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(61,'/article/new-run---kotm-run-for-autism-2022','NEW RUN - KOTM Run For Autism 2022','Kids On The Move recently announced that as of March 31, 2021, the KOTM Autism Center has withdrawn from the Heber Half race.','heber half, run, run for autism, race, 2022, half mile, half marathon, 5k','2021-03-31 11:17:31',3024,'2021-03-31-11-16-pexels-jonas-mohamadi-1416736.jpg','green','article',NULL,NULL),(98,'/event/hearing-screening-2021-06-10','Hearing Screening','<html><head></head><body lang=\"EN-US\" link=\"#0563C1\" vlink=\"#954F72\" style=\"word-wrap&#58;break-word;\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\">We provide a free