INSERT INTO `program_tab_sections` VALUES (1,'I\'m changing the title again',1,'<p>Our Autism Center is designed specifically for parents and children ages 2 and up living with Autism Spectrum Disorders (ASD) or similar developmental delays. Our services, based on principles of Applied Behavior Analysis (ABA), are designed with the child and family in mind. Each child has individual needs to be taken into consideration when deciding what services are appropriate.</p>\n\n<p>We recognize the impact a diagnosis of ASD has on the entire family and offer support to strengthen each family&rsquo;s unique circumstances through a variety of services.</p>\n\n<p>The foundation of all services begins with evidence-based treatment, flexibility and a partnership with parents. To provide the best quality services, we make sure our staff are highly trained, caring professionals. All services are individualized for each client and developed and supervised by Board Certified Behavior Analysts.</p>\n\n<p>We recognize that this is a critical time of development for children and there are many barriers that make it difficult for some children to access needed services. Our goal is to help support parents and children receive the best quality services with a variety of funding options.</p>\n\n<p>We provide the following services in the Kids On The Move Autism Center:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Applied Behavior Analysis Therapy</li>\n	<li>Skill Acquisition and Behavior Reduction Programs</li>\n	<li>In-Clinic and In-Home Services</li>\n	<li>Telehealth Services</li>\n	<li>PEERS Social Skills Course for Teens with Autism</li>\n	<li>Parent Training</li>\n</ul>\n',NULL,NULL,0,'https://members.centralreach.com/?public=true#forms/form?id=29127158-0D8A-44A7-B93A-C8F6242A9CBD','Apply for Services'),(2,'ABA Therapy',1,'<p>All interventions used in the Autism Center fall under the umbrella of applied behavior analysis (ABA). ABA therapy has been used for the treatment of autism since the 1960&rsquo;s and is recognized as effective treatment for autism spectrum disorder (ASD) by the U.S. Surgeon General, the American Academy of Pediatrics, and the National Institute of Health. All ABA services at Kids On The Move are individualized for each client and developed and supervised by Board Certified Behavior Analysts.</p>\n\n<p>ABA therapy works to increase behaviors that are helpful and decrease behaviors that are harmful or affect learning. ABA therapies include Discrete Trial Training, Natural Environment Training, Verbal behavior techniques, and more. ABA therapy can increase skills across many domains such as language, communication, attention, social skills, and daily living skills, as well as decrease problem behaviors.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>ABA therapy can look different depending on the learner. &nbsp;It often involved a lot of play and a focus on increasing language skills. &nbsp;IT can also include working at a table, using token boards, and earning rewards. &nbsp;For some children it may look like practicing daily living skills like preparing a meal, using a fork, potty training, or contributing to the home by doing chores or following a routine. &nbsp;Our treatments are individualized for each child based on their unique strengths and challenges.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:11px\"><strong>Most insurance companies have coverage for ABA therapy and KOTM accepts all major insurances and Medicaid. We also offer self-pay pricing.</strong></p>\n','child_and_therapist_1-min.jpg','article-image-right',1,NULL,NULL),(6,'New Section',7,'<p>some text goes here and stuff</p>\n','031416-autism-kotm-05.JPG','article-image-right',1,'https://google.com','Google it!'),(7,'New Section',0,'',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(8,'New Section',9,'',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(10,'',17,'<p>Put some text here outlining the benefits of applying and maybe the application process</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',2,'https://members.centralreach.com/?public=true#forms/form?id=29127158-0D8A-44A7-B93A-C8F6242A9CBD','Apply for our Autism Center'),(11,'This is a new section',18,'',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(13,'Autism Teen Social Skills (PEERS)',2,'<h4>APPLY NOW FOR INFORMATION ON OUR NEXT AVAILABLE CLASS!&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<p>KOTM provides a social skills class for teens with autism called PEERS. The group is for teens ages 12-18 (middle or high schoolers). This class helps teens who have trouble making friends learn valuable skills about interacting with others.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong><em>Insurance coverage may be available</em></strong></li>\n	<li><strong><em>Private pay rates are $855 for the entire 14 week teen and parent group which includes a graduation party</em></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Teen group from 3:30-5:00 PM</li>\n	<li>Parent Group from 6:00-7:30 PM</li>\n	<li>Groups will be held on Wednesday for 14 consecutive weeks.</li>\n	<li>Teens and parents are expected to complete the entire 14 week program.&nbsp; If more then 2 weeks will be missed, we recommend waiting for a future group.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>TOPICS</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Trading Information</li>\n	<li>Two-way Conversations</li>\n	<li>Electronic Communication</li>\n	<li>Choosing Appropriate Friends</li>\n	<li>Appropriate Use of Humor</li>\n	<li>Entering/Exiting a Conversation</li>\n	<li>Hosting Get-Togethers</li>\n	<li>Good Sportsmanship</li>\n	<li>Dealing with Teasing</li>\n	<li>Dealing with Bullies</li>\n	<li>Handling Disagreements</li>\n	<li>Rumors and Gossip</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>Teen Group</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Teen must be able to participate in Zoom learning independently or with minimal adult support.</li>\n	<li>20 minute homework review</li>\n	<li>25 minute lesson</li>\n	<li>30 minute skill practice/activity</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4><strong>Parent Group</strong></h4>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>50 minute homework review</li>\n	<li>25 minute lesson</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','2021-02-09-12-03-pexels-mary-taylor-5896632.jpg','article-image-right',1,'https://members.centralreach.com/?public=true#forms/form?id=D5450543-53A3-4B0F-A9F5-678145B04B65','Sign up for the Teen Social Skills Class'),(14,'',3,'<p>We are not affiliated with these organizations but here are some additional resources about Autism.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Autism Speaks &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autismspeaks.org/\">http://www.autismspeaks.org/</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Council of Utah &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://autismcouncilofutah.org/\">http://autismcouncilofutah.org/</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Society &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autism-society.org/\">http://www.autism-society.org/</a></li>\n	<li>&ldquo;A Child&rsquo;s Journey Out of Autism&rdquo; Official Website of Leeann Whiffen, &ldquo;A Mother, An Advocate and an Author,&rdquo;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.leeannwhiffen.com/\">http://www.leeannwhiffen.com/</a></li>\n	<li>Utah Parent Center &ndash; &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.utahparentcenter.org/\">http://www.utahparentcenter.org/</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Research Institute &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autism.com/index.asp\">http://www.autism.com/index.asp</a></li>\n	<li>Autism One &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autismone.org/\">http://www.autismone.org/</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Grants for families that have children with autism &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.tacanow.org/family-resources/autism-grants/\">http://www.tacanow.org/family-resources/autism-grants/</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Support Network &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autismsupportnetwork.com/resources/autism-grants-united-states\">http://www.autismsupportnetwork.com/resources/autism-grants-united-states</a></li>\n	<li>Autism Consortium &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.autismconsortium.org/\">http://www.autismconsortium.org/</a></li>\n	<li>Create a Sensory Safe Yard for Children with Special Needs &ndash;&nbsp;<br />\n	<a href=\"https://www.wikilawn.com/blog/landscaping/create-safe-sensory-friendly-backyard-landscape-special-needs-child/\">https://www.wikilawn.com/blog/landscaping/create-safe-sensory-friendly-backyard-landscape-special-needs-child/</a></li>\n	<li>Estate Planning for Parents of Kids with Autism &ndash;<a href=\"https://www.justgreatlawyers.com/estate-planning-for-parents-of-children-with-autism\">https://www.justgreatlawyers.com/estate-planning-for-parents-of-children-with-autism</a></li>\n	<li>How to Calm a Child with Autism &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.verywellhealth.com/how-to-calm-a-child-with-autism-4177696\">https://www.verywellhealth.com/how-to-calm-a-child-with-autism-4177696</a></li>\n</ul>\n','woman-carrying-her-baby-and-working-on-a-laptop-4079281.jpg','article-image-right',1,NULL,NULL),(15,'',19,'<p>We are expanding access to ABA therapy through the use of&nbsp;telehealth technology&nbsp;to close the gap between individuals with autism obtaining this much needed therapy and their geographical location.&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL),(16,'Telehealth ABA Therapy',19,'<p>Kids On The Move has converged the most highly recommended treatment for autism with secure video technology to deliver care in-home, where it is needed most.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4>What is Telehealth?</h4>\n\n<p>Telehealth services are the delivery of ABA therapy to rural communities where there would otherwise be no behavioral healthcare providers to work with children with autism spectrum disorder (ASD). Our BCBAs (Board Certified Behavioral Analysts) have masters&rsquo; level experience and knowledge in training caregivers and working with children.</p>\n\n<p>We believe that all families should have access to the best care for their children. Thanks to our online delivery system, families have immediate access to ABA therapy, eliminating the delays caused by wait-lists, scheduling or geographical location.</p>\n\n<h4>HOW DOES IT WORK?</h4>\n\n<p>Many years of research has been done to find the best way to aid in the physical and mental development of children on the autism spectrum; and Applied Behavior Analysis therapy has continuously been found to be the most effective by taking a look at how human beings learn new things. Additional research has shown that ABA therapy can be is just as effective through telehealth technology as it is in home. &nbsp;in-home as it is through telehealth technology.</p>\n\n<p>To make it all happen our clinicians are equipped with technology that allows for live video and audio streaming as well as data collection.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Some rural locations throughout the state of Utah have well-trained behavior therapist who will carry out the treatment goals during 1:1 therapy in your home, just as our behavior therapists do in a traditional in-home model. &nbsp;The child&rsquo;s BCBA will video conference with the behavior technician during their session so they can oversee the therapy, see the chlid&rsquo;s progress, and make changes to treatment accordingly. The BCBA will also meet with the parent over video conference to provide parent training and to collaborate on goals.&nbsp;<br />\nFor areas in Utah where we do not have local behavior therapists, we are able to offer families an individualized parent training model. &nbsp;The BCBA will train the child&rsquo;s parent to implement ABA therapy techniques, and take data on their child&rsquo;s progress. The BCBA provides the same level of weekly support and training through live video conferencing with the parent, just as we would with our many behavior therapists who implement therapy for our clients in other parts of the state. &nbsp;Dedicated parents who participate in this model are able to become skilled in providing this vital service for their child, with ongoing guidance from a BCBA.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4>HOW CAN YOU GET INVOLVED?</h4>\n\n<p>We always ensure that the parents and caregivers are a part of all treatment sessions where they can learn ABA strategies that can further their child&rsquo;s overall progress in obtaining behavioral goals.&nbsp;<strong>To find out more about these resources in your area, please apply.&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<div class=\"youtube-embed-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;padding-top:30px;height:0;overflow:hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ASVPwNzit0U\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%\" width=\"640\"></iframe></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n','pexels-photo-3818963.jpg','article-image-right',3,'https://members.centralreach.com/?public=true#forms/form?id=29127158-0D8A-44A7-B93A-C8F6242A9CBD','Apply for ABA Therapy'),(17,'Assessment',1,'<p>One of our first steps in designing effective treatment for your child involves an assessment. An assessment for treatment is different from a diagnostic assessment or psychological evaluation. &nbsp;A Board Certified Behavior Analyst (BCBA) will get to know you and your child through a variety of ways, including interviews, observations, skill assessments and questionnaires. &nbsp;All of these items help your child&rsquo;s BCBA better understand your child&rsquo;s strengths and challenges and help guide the course of treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',4,NULL,NULL),(21,'',20,'<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"tel:801.221.9930\">Call Now!&nbsp;</a></p>\n\n<p>Our affordable Orem, UT Child Care Center is a fully-licensed program committed to providing high quality care for children from 6 weeks to first grade enrollment at competitive rates. We have three separate classrooms, separated by age and development.</p>\n\n<p>Our Child Care Orem hours: Monday-Friday 7:30am to 5:30pm.</p>\n\n<h3>Contact us at 801.221.9930 ext. 193&nbsp;to learn more about our Child Care Program and what we can offer your child.&nbsp;</h3>\n\n<h3>GET $50 OFF MAY&#39;S CHILD CARE BY SIGNING UP TODAY!&nbsp;</h3>\n\n<p><strong><em>Need to learn more? Call us at 801.221.9930 or email <a href=\"mailto:mcrowther@kotm.org?subject=KOTM%20Child%20Care\">c</a><a href=\"mailto:childcare@kotm.org?subject=KOTM%20Child%20Care\">hildcare@kotm.org</a></em></strong></p>\n','5230_255-2.jpg','article-image-right',2,NULL,NULL),(27,'Who We Serve',20,'<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px\">We serve Infants, Toddlers and Preschool children where we love, care and empower the children with positive language, engaging activities, focusing on well adjusted happy children and Kindergarten readiness. &nbsp;We understand that a child who feels good about him/herself does better in academics and in life.</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px\">We invite you to come tour our facility to see and feel the difference in KOTM Childcare and other facilities. Call us today to schedule a tour! 801.221.9930.</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:10px\"><a href=\"https://careaboutchildcare.utah.gov/\" target=\"_blank\">Visit Care About Child Care.&nbsp;</a><br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',4,'https://schools.mybrightwheel.com/sign-in?redirect_path=forms/b961611c-7762-444e-95c6-437e48007cab/self-service','Apply Now'),(28,'',24,'<p>At Kids On The Move, we understanding having a young child with special needs, quite often, requires a tremendous amount of time and energy. This is why we offer respite care.</p>\n\n<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"/volunteer-portal\">Sign Up To Volunteer</a>&nbsp;<a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://www.childplus.net/apply/en-us/83DA3460C8B342FA4781195B3D29561E/C73EF6D9004CEA495946B94C3402EEAE\">Apply For Respite Care Services</a></p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(29,'What is Respite Care',24,'<p>Respite Care Utah at Kids On The Move is the temporary care of children with special needs, providing a short period of rest or relief to their usual caregivers. We provide Respite Care for children with special needs to give their families a 3 hour break on weekend nights so caregivers can relieve stress, renew energy, and restore balance.</p>\n',NULL,NULL,2,NULL,NULL),(30,'Who is Eligible',24,'<p>We serve children who are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>birth to 12 years old</li>\n	<li>diagnosed with&nbsp;a special need that is an intellectual, behavioral, or physical disability.</li>\n	<li>able to be at respite until 9:00 p.m. without it disturbing their bedtime routine.</li>\n	<li>not on 100% oxygen or excessively medically fragile.</li>\n	<li>free of a history of sexually inappropriate or aggressive behavior.</li>\n	<li>in a family that does not already have resources that provides them with a break from caregiving.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/e9ng6utiGHw?rel=0\" width=\"640\"></iframe></p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',3,NULL,NULL),(33,'',28,'<p>Times are tough and we all need someone to talk to from time to time. Our therapists provide supportive and empowering therapy via a secure, web-based chat service. This approach allows you to meet with one of our licensed providers from the comfort of your own home and at a convenient time. We can help you address depression, anxiety, stress, life transitions, grief, trauma, and much more.</p>\n\n<p>We accept most major insurances and because mental health needs affect us all our clinicians are ready to help people of all ages. Adults are welcome at Kids On The Move&rsquo;s telehealth therapy program!</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(34,'Mackenzie Pabst',28,'<p>Mackenzie Pabst earned her bachelor&rsquo;s and master&rsquo;s degrees in social work. Her specialty is working with children and teenagers struggling with a variety of issues including trauma, grief and loss, anxiety, depression, and family stressors. Mackenzie uses Play Therapy, EMDR, TF-CBT, and Strengths-based techniques to help clients and families heal and achieve their goals.</p>\n','2021-02-09-09-23-headshot mackenzie.jpg','article-image-right',2,NULL,NULL),(35,'',21,'<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://www.childplus.net/apply/en-us/315E187AF9E07E8BA1C6E2F168B43DF7/5772193B8EE7FBF557556E473C56020E\">Child Application&nbsp;</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class=\"btn\" href=\"/form/early-head-start\">Pregnant Mom Application</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class=\"btn\" href=\"https://www.childplus.net/apply/es/315E187AF9E07E8BA1C6E2F168B43DF7/5772193B8EE7FBF557556E473C56020E\">Child Application (Spanish)</a></p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(36,'What is Early Head Start?',21,'<p>Give your child the very best start in life with Early Head Start. Early Head Start is designed to nurture and support your child&rsquo;s physical, social, emotional &amp; intellectual development, from birth to age three.</p>\n\n<p>Prenatal services are part of our resources. We also provide parenting and nutrition classes so parents can learn valuable skills to support their baby&rsquo;s growth and development.</p>\n\n<p>Infants as young as six weeks old can enroll in the Early Head Start program. For very young children, every moment is an opportunity for learning. Our Early Head Start staff are specially trained in early childhood development. We read &amp; talk to your infants, and toddlers to build vocabulary, encourage them to explore their world through play, song, touch, sight &amp; sound. We use routine and structure to help them feel safe and build trust. In addition, we provide families with resources to support healthy development and learning at home, family health &amp; nutrition and coordinate services for children with special needs. When your child turns three, they will be prepared to transition to Head Start or another appropriate preschool program to continue their path to learning success.</p>\n\n<p>Early Head Start supports your infant and toddler&rsquo;s early development through:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Education </strong>&ndash; Your child will learn through fun games, songs, and activities. We help them reach early milestones such as making friends and playing with others, using their fingers and hands, following directions, expressing themselves, and showing an interest in learning. We utilize evidence &amp; research based curriculum &amp; assessments in both center-based and home based services.</li>\n	<li><strong>Family Services</strong> &ndash; Our staff works with you to create family goals and create a plan to meet those goals. We also connect you to additional resources in your community.</li>\n	<li><strong>Health Services</strong> &ndash; Nothing is more important than your child&rsquo;s health! We&rsquo;ll work with you to make sure your child receives regular medical and dental check-ups, and can help you find free or affordable services in your area. We make getting the care your child needs a priority.</li>\n	<li><strong>Prenatal Care and Education</strong> &ndash; For moms-to-be, we provide services and resources such as prenatal nutrition and parenting classes. Learn how to fully care for your newborn as well as yourself. It&rsquo;s never too early to start!</li>\n	<li><strong>Nutrition</strong> &ndash; Healthy eating fuels growing minds and bodies! We provide healthy meals and snacks, and evaluate each child&rsquo;s nutritional needs. We also work with our children and families to encourage healthy choices and provide resources for home.</li>\n	<li><strong>Special Needs</strong> &ndash; We work with every child to understand their unique needs. Children of all abilities, including those with special needs, are welcomed, supported, and included in all activities in the classroom or home. Our staff will also help connect your family to the additional resources that can best support your child.</li>\n</ul>\n','2021-02-09-11-39-_DSC0024-54.jpg','article-image-right',3,NULL,NULL),(37,'Who is Eligible?',21,'<p>Pregnant mothers and children birth to three years of age.</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',4,NULL,NULL),(38,'',21,'',NULL,'article-image-left',2,'','Pregnant Mom Application'),(39,'Enrollment Process',21,'<p>Enrollment is determined on a case by case basis. We look at several factors, not limited to: Income guidelines, Family Need, Disability of the Child, Foster Care, Homelessness, etc.</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',5,NULL,NULL),(40,'Parent In-Kind Form',21,'<p>How can parents help give back to KOTM EHS?<br />\n&bull; Parents track time spent working with their child towards individualized development goals.<br />\n&bull; Parents can volunteer in the classroom,<br />\n&bull; Parents can help implement Home-based PlaySchool<br />\n&bull; Parents can help prepare learning materials to be used in classrooms, during PlaySchool and/or home visits</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',6,NULL,NULL),(41,'',22,'<p>No two children are the same&mdash;each one is unique. And that&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s sometimes hard to tell when you should be concerned about differences between infants and toddlers of the same age. &nbsp;Most differences are nothing to worry about, but in some children the differences can signal a need for Early Intervention.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(42,'What is Early Intervention?',22,'<p>When you contact Kids On The Move, our caring professionals will listen to your concerns and conduct a full developmental assessment of your child at no cost. &nbsp;Eligible children will receive services to help them grow and learn during the first 3 years of life. &nbsp;Services include developmental assessments, physical therapy, occupational therapy, speech and language therapy, hearing and vision assessment, nursing, nutrition and parent training classes. &nbsp;Most Early Intervention services will be provided at a convenient time for your family in your home or other familiar places where your child learns and plays.</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',2,'/form/early-intervention/','Apply for Free Consultation'),(43,'Who is Eligible?',22,'<p>Children residing in the Alpine School District under the age of three with a significant delay in one or more of the following areas:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Physical development</li>\n	<li>Vision and hearing</li>\n	<li>Feeding</li>\n	<li>Social and emotional development</li>\n	<li>Communication and language</li>\n	<li>Learning, problem solving and play skills</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Many children with a diagnosed medical condition also qualify for services.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',3,NULL,NULL),(44,'Early Intervention Program Services',29,'<h4>COMPREHENSIVE INITIAL EVALUATION</h4>\n\n<p>Finding out what your child does well and what concerns there are is the first step in helping your child develop new skills. We tailor the initial evaluation to meet your family needs. We will look at all areas of development including health, hearing and vision. The evaluation typically includes administering a nationally accepted test, observation of your child in your home and with your permission we may ask to collect relevant information from other professionals, such as your doctor.</p>\n\n<h4>NURSE</h4>\n\n<p>A registered nurse comes to your home to do a health, hearing and vision assessment as part of the overall assessment. We learn about your child&rsquo;s current health, hearing and vision status which helps us design the needed services, if your child is eligible for Early Intervention services.</p>\n\n<h4>INDIVIDUALIZED FAMILY SERVICE PLAN</h4>\n\n<p>Parents develop a plan that lists child and family goals as well as the services and supports needed to reach the goals. Goals can include things such as helping a child meet a developmental milestone, improving interactions with siblings, finding parent support, or interaction with other parents. The plan is reviewed and updated every 6 months.</p>\n\n<h4>SERVICE COORDINATION</h4>\n\n<p>Service Coordinators will assist the family in finding and getting needed services by linking to other resources in the community and implementing your child&rsquo;s Individualized Family Service Plan.</p>\n\n<h4>HOME VISITS</h4>\n\n<p>Certified and licensed professionals come to your home and together you will plan learning experiences and activities to support your child&rsquo;s growth and development.</p>\n\n<h4>DEVELOPMENTAL SPECIALIST</h4>\n\n<p>A credentialed Early Intervention Specialist is trained to address all areas of development with an emphasis in social-emotional, thinking and learning skills. They will work with you and your child to optimize your child&rsquo;s development.</p>\n\n<h4>OCCUPATIONAL THERAPY</h4>\n\n<p>A licensed Occupational Therapist will help you work on your child&rsquo;s fine motor, sensory, self-help and feeding skills.</p>\n\n<h4>PHYSICAL THERAPY</h4>\n\n<p>A licensed Physical Therapist will help you work on your child&rsquo;s motor development, strength, coordination, balance and functional abilities.</p>\n\n<h4>SPEECH AND LANGUAGE THERAPY</h4>\n\n<p>A licensed Speech Language Pathologist will work with your child to address delays in communication, language, speech, emergent literacy and or feeding/swallowing skills, through early intervention speech therapy.</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',2,NULL,NULL),(45,'',29,'<p>If your child qualifies for the Kids On The Move&nbsp;early intervention program, he or she may receive a variety of services based on their individual needs.&nbsp; Not all children in the program receive every service since Early Intervention services are determined by the child&rsquo;s individual developmental needs.&nbsp; If your child qualifies for services, you may be charged a participation fee based on a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://health.utah.gov/cshcn/pdf/BabyWatch/Sliding Fee Scale.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">sliding&nbsp;fee scale</a>.&nbsp; The cost ranges from $0-$200 per month.&nbsp; Depending on your child&rsquo;s needs his, or her early intervention services may include the following services.</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',1,NULL,NULL),(46,'Classes & Playgroups',29,'<p>Parent Training classes are open to enrolled and general public families depending upon availability. There may be a small fee included.</p>\n\n<h4>PARENT-CHILD PLAYGROUPS</h4>\n\n<p>The child is accompanied by a parent or caregiver in a social environment which supports the parent-child relationship in ways that are tailored to the particular learning needs of the children and parents in the group.</p>\n\n<h4>INFANT MASSAGE</h4>\n\n<p>A one-time class (1 1/2 hours) taught by a Certified Infant Massage Instructor (CIMI). Parents bring baby with them as they learn and practice massage techniques and sequences established by Loving Touch Foundation. Infant massage cultivates love, compassion, respect and well-being for infants and children through touch.</p>\n\n<h4>GREAT BEGINNINGS</h4>\n\n<p>This parent class meets once a week (1 1/2 hours) for 2&nbsp;weeks. Parents learn about their child&rsquo;s communication, hearing, and language development. Class also includes training in basic strategies to promote language development and how to work these strategies into daily routines at home.</p>\n\n<h4>FLOORTIME</h4>\n\n<p>This parent class meets once a week (1 1/2 hours) for 3 weeks. Parents learn how to enhance communication between parent and child through play and social interactions with an emphasis in problem solving and complex communication strategies.</p>\n\n<h4>SIBSHOPS</h4>\n\n<p>This recreational workshop is for children ages 7-13 who have a sibling with special needs. They enjoy a spirited mix of fun games, making new friends, discussion/education activities and lunch.&nbsp; They share the joys and frustrations of having a sibling with special needs.&nbsp;Sibshops are held monthly at Kids On The Move on the second Saturday of each month from 10:00-12:30.&nbsp; We serve all families in the community and the cost is $5 per child or covered by Kids On The Move if under an IFSP.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',3,'/events','View Classes Calendar'),(48,'More Information',2,'<p>PEERS originally started at UCLA and had a high proven success rate. At the end of the 14 week program, teens with autism reported having more peer interactions outside of school and increased the number of get-togethers they hosted. Some even showed a significant decrease in their autism symptoms (related to social responsiveness) after attending PEERS (Laugeson, Frankel, Gantman, Dillon &amp; Mogil 2011).</p>\n\n<p>The group doesn&rsquo;t just involve the teenagers, however. It requires parent involvement so that the students can continue to learn outside of the group. This helps teens obtain social skills that are long-lasting and will positively affect the rest of their lives.</p>\n\n<p><b>Now accepting applications for 2021 classes.</b>&nbsp;To learn more contact Mia Pieper at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:mpieper@kotm.org\">mpieper@kotm.org</a>&nbsp;or call 801-221-9930 ext. 209 or complete the online application to sign-up.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Click&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XZEMUtcJnhg\">here</a>&nbsp;to watch founder of PEERS, Dr. Elizabeth Laugeson, share her tips on how to combat bullies.</strong></p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',2,'https://members.centralreach.com/?public=true#forms/form?id=D5450543-53A3-4B0F-A9F5-678145B04B65','Apply for PEERS'),(49,'Financial Resources for Families',3,'<p>Even with insurance coverage, we understand that ABA therapy can be expensive. &nbsp;The following grants are not affiliated with Kids On The Move but may be a resource for families in covering the cost of ABA therapy.</p>\n\n<h4>Active Grants That&nbsp;Can Apply Towards Co-insurance and Co-pays<br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.modestneeds.org/for-applicants/index.asp\">Modest Needs</a> &ndash; $750-$1,250</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>This grant is tailored to individuals and families living just above the poverty line but are ineligible for most types of social assistance</li>\n	<li>One-time assistance</li>\n	<li>Grant can be applied towards co-insurance and co-pays<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://mygoalautism.org/mygoal-resources/#grants\">MyGOAL Inc</a> &ndash; $1,000</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>This grant is offered in December every year and distributed the following Spring</li>\n	<li>Upload W-9 or recent tax return</li>\n	<li>Can be applied to co-insurance and co-pays<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.uhccf.org/apply-for-a-grant/\">United Healthcare Children&rsquo;s Foundation</a> &ndash; Up to $5000 in one year. Can reapply each year and receive up to $10,000 as a lifetime maximum</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>16 years old or younger</li>\n	<li>Must have SSN</li>\n	<li>Family must not exceed maximum eligible family income as documented on IRS Tax Form 1040</li>\n	<li>Primary coverage for the child must be by a commercial health plan. Secondary insurance through Medicaid or CHIP is permissible<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.versustexas.com/scholarships/\">Varghese Summersett PLLC Annual Scholarships</a> &ndash; $500 Submit all materials to Melody Lanier at <a href=\"mailto:melody@versustexas.com\">melody@versustexas.com</a></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>15 years old or younger</li>\n	<li>Autism Diagnosis</li>\n	<li>Must submit letter or video stating how the scholarship will benefit them.<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Additional Grant Options<br />\n&nbsp;</h4>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.firsthandfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/US-Application.pdf\">Firsthand Foundation</a> &ndash; $1250-$2500</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>18 years or younger (age 19-21 considered if child-like mental state)</li>\n	<li>No existing insurance coverage for requested expenses</li>\n	<li>Household income: Dependents\n	<ul>\n		<li>5 &ndash; Up to $100k</li>\n		<li>4 &ndash; Up to $85k</li>\n		<li>3 &ndash; Up to $70k</li>\n		<li>2 &ndash; Up to $55k</li>\n		<li>1 &ndash; Up to $40k</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Can be used to assist with stand of car for child&rsquo;s diagnosis</li>\n	<li>Cannot pay co-insurance, co-pays, past bills, or debts<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://nebula.wsimg.com/24e88818a52433cb7f1c373311b38c03?AccessKeyId=B82736982722AF60CDE0&amp;disposition=0&amp;alloworigin=1\">KNOW Autism &ndash; Tuition and Therapy Assistance Program</a> &ndash; $1000-$3000</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>18 months &ndash; 18 years old</li>\n	<li>For families in need of financial assistance</li>\n	<li>Must be medically diagnosed with ASD</li>\n	<li>Must be attending a special needs school or program &ndash; ABA therapy, special needs camp, special needs school, speech or occupational therapy</li>\n	<li>CANNOT be applied to coinsurance and copays, only towards the facility<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://nebula.wsimg.com/475c017481fd25ed9cbf33d6048b72ad?AccessKeyId=B82736982722AF60CDE0&amp;disposition=0&amp;alloworigin=1\">KNOW Autism &ndash; Autism Diagnostic Assistance Program</a> &ndash; $500-$750</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>This scholarship is specifically for DIAGNOSTIC TESTING fees, for testing an individual for ASD</li>\n	<li>18 months &ndash; 10 years old<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://nebula.wsimg.com/da73050b46765992f5e346f6091cf69a?AccessKeyId=B82736982722AF60CDE0&amp;disposition=0&amp;alloworigin=1\">KNOW Autism &ndash; Special Interest Fund</a></strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>This fund is specifically for adaptive programs outside the traditional umbrella of autism treatments (not ABA)</li>\n	<li>Between 12 months and 18 years</li>\n	<li>Eligible programs:\n	<ul>\n		<li>Equine therapy, special needs camps/summer programs, adaptive sports, adaptive dance, adaptive swim lessons, etc.</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Must provide ASD diagnosis</li>\n	<li>CANNOT be applied to coinsurance and copays, only towards the facility<br />\n	&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://myasdf.org/our-programs/holiday-gift-card-program/\">ASDF&rsquo;s Holiday Gift Card Program (Check back Oct 1st, 2020 for open application)</a> &ndash; $100 Gift Card</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>For families with great need for financial assistance who have individuals in the family on the spectrum</li>\n</ul>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',2,NULL,NULL),(50,'Donating to Respite Care',24,'<p><strong>- Donate financially: </strong><a href=\"http://www.kotm.org/donate\">www.kotm.org/donate</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>- Donate in-kind:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Goldfish crackers,</li>\n	<li>Welch&rsquo;s fruit snacks (Welch&#39;s has the preferred texture for our clients and is gluten free),</li>\n	<li>Water bottles</li>\n	<li>Popular board games</li>\n	<li>New hard plastic toys with no small pieces.</li>\n</ul>\n','2021-04-15-14-40-banner-goldfish-chedder_v4.jpg','article-image-left',4,NULL,NULL),(52,'Pricing',30,'<h3>GET $50 OFF MAY&#39;S CHILD CARE BY SIGNING UP TODAY!&nbsp;</h3>\n\n<h4>0-18 months</h4>\n\n<p>$958 per month</p>\n\n<h4>18 months - 3 years</h4>\n\n<p>$958 per month</p>\n\n<h4>3-4 years</h4>\n\n<p>$775 per month potty trained /&nbsp;$958 per month&nbsp;not potty trained&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4>4-6 years Full Time</h4>\n\n<p>$775 per month (must be potty trained)</p>\n\n<h4>4-6 years Part Time</h4>\n\n<p>$388 per month for morning or for afternoon (must be potty trained)</p>\n','2021-04-16-12-07-(10).jpg','article-image-left',1,'https://schools.mybrightwheel.com/sign-in?redirect_path=forms/b961611c-7762-444e-95c6-437e48007cab/self-service','Apply Now'),(53,'Our Program',20,'<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://youtu.be/y1MjclC1RQ8\" /><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/y1MjclC1RQ8?rel=0\" width=\"640\"></iframe></p>\n',NULL,'article-image-left',5,NULL,NULL),(54,'Music & Movement Class',23,'<p>Don&#39;t miss out on our Music &amp; Movement class happening on Wednesdays and Fridays from 10:30 a.m. - 11:00 a.m.! This is a great class for your toddler. If you&#39;re interested in your child building literacy and communication skills through songs, finger plays, group book reading and movement activities - you need to attend these classes! Email Jessica Nix to learn more and to get the zoom link: jnix@kotm.org</p>\n\n<p><a class=\"btn\" href=\"mailto:jnix@kotm.org?subject=Music%20%26%20Movement%20Class\">Learn More</a></p>\n','2021-04-22-13-50-krakenimages-Br-ayoAxFuQ-unsplash.jpg','article-image-right',3,NULL,NULL),(55,'Step-Families Class',23,'<p>Join us for a FREE educational program focusing on issues unique to step-family relationships. Concurrent classes for adults and youth 6-18. There will also be FREE dinner and childcare available! This class is on Thursdays, May 6 - June 17 from&nbsp;6:00 - 8:00 p.m. at the&nbsp;Kids On The Move building in&nbsp;Orem. Questions? Email acecil@kotm.org</p>\n','2021-02-09-09-23-allen-taylor-0cmJRW5rOJ8-unsplash horiz.jpg','article-image-left',4,'/form/step-families','Learn More'),(56,'Autism PEERS Teen Class',23,'<p>KOTM provides a social skills class for teens with autism called PEERS. The group is for teens ages 12-18 (middle or high schoolers). This class helps teens who have trouble making friends learn valuable skills about interacting with others.</p>\n','2021-04-22-13-50-naassom-azevedo-Q_Sei-TqSlc-unsplash.jpg','article-image-right',5,'/programs/autism-center/teen-social-skills-(peers)','Learn More');
